spanishExample: Nos encantarían más perros.
englishTranslation: We would love more dogs.

spanishExample: Nos encantaban esos libros, así que creo que nos encantará la película.
englishTranslation: We used to love those books, so I think we’ll love the movie.

spanishExample: Nos encantará ir al bosque.
englishTranslation: We’ll love going to the forest.

spanishExample: Te va a encantar esta película.
englishTranslation: You are going to love this movie.

spanishExample: Ha estado tocando la guitarra por horas.
englishTranslation: She has been playing the guitar for hours.

spanishExample: ¡No toque eso! No le encantó la última vez.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Don’t touch that! You didn't love it last time.

spanishExample: Este consejo basta para nuestro proyecto.
englishTranslation: This piece of advice does the trick for our project.

spanishExample: No quiero que toquen ningún juego, salvo este.
englishTranslation: I don’t want them to touch any game, except this one.

spanishExample: No ha tocado el piano en un tiempo.
englishTranslation: She hasn’t played the piano in a while.

spanishExample: No quiero que toques esa canción durante la tormenta.
englishTranslation: I don’t want you to play that song during the storm.

spanishExample: Tocó ese juego porque le encantó.
englishTranslation: He touched that game because he loved it.

spanishExample: Si tocas su brazo, le dolerá.
englishTranslation: If you touch her arm, it will hurt her.

spanishExample: Me han encantado todos esos juegos.
englishTranslation: I have loved all those games.

spanishExample: Mi mamá no quiere que toque el mar.
englishTranslation: My mom doesn’t want me to touch the sea.

spanishExample: Me encantaba el bosque, sobre todo con lluvia.
englishTranslation: I used to love the forest, especially with rain.

spanishExample: El brazo me dolió por el sol en la playa.
englishTranslation: My arm hurt me because of the sun at the beach.

spanishExample: Está a salvo aunque le duele la cabeza por ir tras ella.
englishTranslation: He is safe even though his head hurts because of going after her.

spanishExample: Me encantan esas islas y me encantaría volver ahí.
englishTranslation: I love those islands and I would love to go back there.

spanishExample: Al parecer, dos personas bastan para el trabajo.
englishTranslation: Apparently, two people are enough for the job.

spanishExample: Ante un problema, tu consejo bastaría.
englishTranslation: In the face of a problem, your advice would do the trick.

spanishExample: Le encantan la luna y el río.
englishTranslation: She loves the moon and the river.

spanishExample: Le bastaba una cosa.
englishTranslation: One thing did the trick for him.

spanishExample: Les ha bastado un perro para estar salvos y felices.
englishTranslation: One dog has done the trick for them to be safe and happy.

spanishExample: La música suena bien cuando yo la toco.
englishTranslation: The music sounds good when I play it.

spanishExample: Te toca; te encantaba jugar esto antes.
englishTranslation: It’s your turn; you used to love playing this before.

spanishExample: Nos han encantado todos los árboles.
englishTranslation: We have loved all the trees.

spanishExample: Ese dinero podría bastar y me encantaría tenerlo.
englishTranslation: That money could do the trick and I would love to have it.

spanishExample: Esto podría doler, entonces solo uno no bastará.
englishTranslation: This could hurt, so just one won’t do the trick.

spanishExample: ¡No toques eso! No me encanta.
englishTranslation: Don’t play that! I don’t love it.

spanishExample: El teléfono tiene que sonar para que ellos lo toquen.
englishTranslation: The phone has to ring in order for them to touch it.

spanishExample: Una sola canción basta; suenas enfermo.
englishTranslation: Just one song is enough; you sound sick.

spanishExample: Te va a encantar el lago, porque te encanta la naturaleza.
englishTranslation: You’re going to love the lake, because you love nature.

spanishExample: Bastaban dos plantas al lado de la casa para eso.
englishTranslation: Two plants beside the house did the trick for that.
